Swanton School’s office hours are limited during the summer months.

Our front office is primarily staffed from

8:00 am to 12:00 pm, Monday through Friday.

Outside of these hours, you can leave a message for the Main Office by calling 868-5346, and someone will respond the following business day. You can also always reach us through email. BE safe and have a great summer. We appreciate ALL that you did this spring! #WeRSwanton

Parents of Sixth Graders, tomorrow night, TUESDAY, JUNE 9 is our Recognition/Celebration Night. You should have received ALL the information about this night.

We plan to leave the school at 5:00 pm and will follow the route we shared with you. It will have to be a VERY QUICK STOP...as we are trying to make 70 stops in three hours!

If you could be outside your home and ready to greet the bus and the "little parade" that would be great. Your child's teacher will hand your child his/her school belongings and goodie bag from our sixth grade parent group.

If your child could be ready to hand back in his/her chromebook and any library or classroom books to return that would help.

We are excited to celebrate our sixth graders! The weather promises to be nice as well!

post_text:
hey all-

not sure when your last day of school is, so i figured i would send this out now so you can get to students, families, etc at the right time.

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1JoEBV1H9u21KXIvA9x4UsFr6rtv8G9HR/view?usp=sharing

i have had so much fun sharing time with you and your students, in person when i could, electronically when we had to. it has been such an honor to be invited into your classroom to participate in learning together. i loved the laughter, the epiphanies, the ability to be ok with making mistakes and using it to make discoveries, and the enthusiasm to share it with each other.

happy last days, happy summer, happy every days.

may kindness be your go-to

~moretti

Every day, you and your Teacher Friends face unprecedented challenges – and every day, you teach on.

post_text:
IT IS KINDERGARTEN REGISTRATION TIME!
If your child will be turning five (5) on or before
September 1, 2020 he/she
is eligible to attend Kindergarten in the fall.

What is Registration? Registration is the first step to enrolling your child at Swanton School. Please take a moment to call the school 868-5346 Monday-Friday between 7:30-9:30 or email Justina.jennett@mvsdschools.org to request a registration packet for the 2020-2021 school year. We will mail it out to you and you can mail it back to us as soon as possible. In order for your child to attend school the Vermont Department of Health requires that you provide a COPY of:
Birth Certificate
Immunization Records
If you HAVE a completed registration packet, PLEASE mail it back to the school as soon as you can! 24 Fourth Street, Swanton, VT 05488. Any questions? Let us know.

post_text: Yesterday we celebrated Indigenous Peoples Day @SwantonSchool. We also got to celebrate our new Outdoor Classroom. post_text:
Please join us on September 7th from 10am until Dusk to celebrate the arts! From 10 until 5 we will have 50 booths set up in Swanton Village on the Green with crafts/arts/foods and hands on fun! There will be live music all day, a pet parade, a pancake eating contest and so much more! We will end the SPECTACULAR day with Fireworks over the evolving Marble Mill Park!

Please check out our facebook page and the Swanton Arts Council website for more details on times and activities.

For questions please contact SAS@SwantonArtsCouncil.org

post_text:
REMEMBER to get out and vote TUESDAY, APRIL 30! Here is a message from our current School Board Chair:

This is to inform you about the vote that is taking place this Tuesday, April 30th. The vote has the potential for long-term impact on MVSD (Missisquoi Valley School District) and the town of Swanton. The vote has two articles:

1. Board member selection for the new MVSD board (Meaghan Conly and Don Collins, two current Swanton School Board members, are running unopposed for Swanton).

2. Approval of amended Articles of Agreement

post_text:
Have you considered a donation to the Swanton School Playground Fund?

We continue to fundraise to create a new, safe and FUN outdoor experience for our students and local community. A special THANK YOU to Peoples Trust Company for their recent donation of $10,000. Talk about amazing community support! And a SHOUT OUT to the Swanton PTO, who has been planning to support this project for a long time. Their donation of $35,000 was a great boost. TOGETHER WE CAN DO THIS! Thank you so much to these two great organizations.

If you would like more information on our playground project, or would like to purchase an engraved brick, please call the school at 868-4920.

shared_text:
Sheldon Elementary School
January 16, 2019 at 6:35 PM ·

Families impacted by the government shutdown. Please contact us about helping out with your students' lunch. Did you know parents are encouraged to submit new F&R applications at any point in the year when financial circumstances change, including because of a furlough, job loss, reduction in hours, etc. Reapply using your most current income information. Once approved for benefits, families will continue to qualify for the benefits for the rest of the school year (plus 30 days of the next school year), regardless of when circumstances improve.

Please contact us at 933-4909 and chat with Kalen.

post_text: We are so excited to announce that a former Swanton School student, Tom Rugg and his wife Kate, are generously matching all donations to the Swanton Playground Fund received by January 31, 2019, up to $2500. The Rugg Family is donating these funds in honor of their mother, Myrielle Blouin Rugg who worked in the Swanton school system for over 20 years. Please help us meet this challenge by donating online at swantonschool.org. Please spread the word! Every donation counts! Thank you for your support of the Swanton Playground Fund.

Swanton Skating Rink Update: It will take a bit for the ice to freeze, so it will be early to mid week before we give the go ahead for anyone to use the rink. Please stay off the rink until we give the all clear- which we will share on our Facebook page.

post_text:
Our Buy a Brick campaign is LIVE! Your purchase of an engraved brick will help to fund our new playground, while leaving your permanent mark on the Swanton community. These bricks will be placed at the new entrance to the playground off the Fit & Healthy Path. An investment in Swanton's playground is an investment in the next generation. Swanton students will have more information in their Wednesday Weekly this week. You may also access the link below.
Thank you for your support!

https://www.fundraisingbrick.com/online-orders/swantonplayground/
